These safeguards have been built as part of the aqueous ammonia storage facility.  The ammonia area monitoring sensors that have been installed in the aqueous ammonia storage facility area and near the ammonia vaporizer skid are used to monitor ambient ammonia concentrations to detect leaks or spills of ammonia.  Alarms are designed to annunciate in the control room with local audible alarms for ammonia releases at the facility.

To minimize impacts from accidental releases, workers have been trained in the safe handling of hazardous materials, use of response equipment, procedures for mitigation of a release, and coordination with local emergency response organizations.  To avoid or minimize impacts from an accidental release of hazardous materials, non-hazardous or less hazardous materials are used, where possible, and engineering controls have been implemented.  For example, aqueous ammonia was selected for the SCR system over anhydrous ammonia, because it is less hazardous.

