1.6.4	Training
The Training Coordinator is responsible for implementing, updating and documenting all of the operator training programs at CCGS.  An effective training program is essential to safe, efficient operations with hazardous materials such as aqueous ammonia.  Proper training is beneficial to the release prevention program in that it provides operators with a clear understanding of how to safely operate the SCR system and therefore significantly reduce the number of equipment malfunctions and incidents that could result in injuries or releases of aqueous ammonia.  A thorough training program also increases the awareness of the hazards associated with aqueous ammonia and provides operators with the knowledge of how to identify, correct and avoid deviations from normal and safe operating conditions, which also reduces the number and severity of incidents.

